article.description: Dallas Moore scored 20 points and added a team-high five assists to help lead North Florida to an 80-72 win over Trinity Baptist on Monday night.
article.headline: North Florida puts away Trinity Baptist, 80-72
article.linkText: North Florida puts away Trinity Baptist, 80-72
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. -- Dallas Moore scored 20 points and added a team-high five assists to help lead North Florida to an 80-72 win over Trinity Baptist on Monday night. Beau Beech added 16 points and eight rebounds and Demarcus Daniels finished with 13 points for the Ospreys (6-2), who have won three straight following a two-game losing streak. North Florida shot 46.7% from the field, hit 11 3-pointers, and had 20 team assists. Trinity Baptist led much of the first half, but Moore and Daniels hit back-to-back 3-pointers in the final 1:29 to give North Florida a 36-34 lead at the break. The Osprey's put together a 19-11 stretch over the first eight minutes of the second half, capped by a Trent Mackey trey which extended their lead to 10 (57-47). Darnel Antoine led the Eagles with 21 points.
